    "language": "en",
    "description": "We've got a simple lil Flapjack recipe for you. Well, simple in method but seriously COMPLEX in flavour. These Caramelised White Chocolate and Pecan Flapjacks can be adapted to suit you (maybe you don't have time to caramelise the white chocolate or want it to have dark chocolate instead? Go for it!) and take no time at all to whip up. They're also great for family baking days!\n\nHappy Baking! x\n\n8\" Square Tin (or something similar)\n\nIngredients\n250g Oats\n125g Soft Unsalted Butter\n125g Light Brown Sugar\n65g Golden Syrup\nPinch of Sea Salt\n1/2 tsp Cinnamon\n60g Toasted Pecan Nuts\n60g Caramelised White Chocolate\n\n-----------\nBecome a Patreon BAKE CLUB member for a pdf download of this and other recipes, as well as Bake-Alongs, extra content, baking tips and more.\n\nBAKE CLUB: http://patreon.com/cupcakejemma\nBAKE AT HOME: http://cupcakejemma\nCAKES: http://www.crumbsanddoilies.co.uk \nINSTAGRAM: @cupcakejemma \nCAKESTAGRAM: @crumbsanddoilies",
